<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head densely and minutely punctured dorsally, clypeus sparsely punctured, surface smooth with strong luster; anterior incisions of clypeus deep and round; labrum small, broader than long; malar space 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of middle ocellus; postocellar area 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long; without middle furrow; lateral furrows narrow, subparallel; POL: OOL: OCL = 5: 8: 11. Head clearly dilated behind eye in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12C, F</figureCitation>
). Antenna about 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than head breadth, club breadth about 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
apical breadth of antennomere 3, club length 1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of antennomere 3, antennomere 3 as long as the longest axis of eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesonotum, mesopleuron deeply and densely punctured, interspace between punctures microsculptured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12E, I</figureCitation>
). Notauli broad and deep; lower margin of metapleuron with obtuse oblique carina; mesoscutellum roundly elevated without middle furrow; cenchri elliptical, distance between cenchri about 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
the longest axis of a cenchrus; metascutellum triangularly protruded upwards (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal terga with fine and dense microsculptures (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12L, M</figureCitation>
). Tergum 1 with distinct lateral carina at anterior 2/3, hind corner pointed, distinctly protruded, posterior margin broadly and very deeply incised to a depth about 3/4 lateral length of tergum; middle process of sternum 7 broad, apex roundish, basal breadth about 1/3 breadth of sternite 7. Lancet with 42 serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12N</figureCitation>
); middle serrulae distinctly narrowed toward blunt apex with 4-5 proximal and 5-6 distal subbasal teeth, distance between serrulae 2.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal breadth of a serrula (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12O</figureCitation>
); lance short and broad, subapical annuli feebly broadened, total length of annuli 3.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height of 13th annulus, first annulus 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 20 mm (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12B</figureCitation>
). Body color and structures similar to female, but differs from the latter in the following characters: fore coxae and femora distinctly prolonged (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12P</figureCitation>
), middle and hind coxae and femora distinctly enlarged and extended, coxae prismatic with edges, shiny. Subgenital plate roundish at apex. Penis valve broad as shown in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Asicimbex nanjingensis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., A holotype female in dorsal view B allotype male in dorsal view C head of female in front view D head of male in front view E thoracic notum F head of female in dorsal view G head of male in dorsal view H antenna of female I mesopleuron and metapleuron J gonoforceps K penis valve L abdominal terga M lateral side of abdomen N lancet O middle serrulae P coxa and femur of male." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707235" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">12K</figureCitation>
, gonoforceps as shown in Fig. 
